<div id="black-friday-marketing-stats-and-facts"></div>
<h2>Why your business needs a Black Friday marketing and advertising strategy</h2>
<p><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/black-friday-marketing-ideas/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Black Friday marketing and advertising</a> should be a no-brainer for every business out there, even if your industry doesn‚Äôt directly connect back to holiday shopping. Here are some key Black Friday marketing statistics and facts that explain why.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/2753.png" alt="‚ùì" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />Are your PPC campaigns ready to take on Black Friday?</strong> Find out with a free, instant account report from our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Grader</a>!</p>
<h3>Black Friday drives revenue for businesses (regardless of industry)</h3>
<p>Black Friday online sales grew by <a href="https://www.salesforce.com/news/press-releases/2024/12/04/cyber-week-ai-sales/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">5%</a> year over year with global sales reaching $74.4 billion in 2024. Sales across all of Cyber Week increased by 7% totaling $314.9 billion. Plus, nearly <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">60%</a> of businesses see a significant lift in sales during the holidays.</p>
<p>In fact, <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">73%</a> of businesses report that 20% of their annual revenue comes from Black Friday, Cyber Monday, Christmas, and New Year campaigns. 28% of businesses say the holidays account for 30 to 50% of their revenue, and 8% attribute the peak holiday season to over 50% of revenue.</p>
<h3>Black Friday deals can attract new customers to your business</h3>
<p>Your Black Friday marketing and advertising can help you tap into audiences you might not always reach year-round. For example, if you‚Äôre primarily an in-store or in-office operation looking to grow online, you can use Black Friday to gain traction for your mobile site as <a href="https://www.salesforce.com/news/press-releases/2024/12/04/cyber-week-ai-sales/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">70%</a> of Black Friday purchases are made on a mobile device.</p>
<h3>Consumers (and competitors) have Black Friday top-of-mind early on</h3>
<p>Having a Black Friday marketing strategy ready to go sets you up for success and gets you ahead of the holiday game. Over <a href="https://www.bcg.com/press/14november2024-consumers-black-friday-genai-shop-bargains" target="_blank" rel="noopener">60%</a> of holiday shoppers start their buyer‚Äôs journey in October or early November. Plus, <a href="https://www.mailgun.com/blog/email/bfcm-stats-2023/">57%</a> of consumers say they prefer to get details about holiday discounts in advance. In other words, knowing what Black Friday deals to expect beforehand is a priority for most shoppers.</p>
<p>Your customers aren‚Äôt the only ones with Black Friday top-of-mind early on, either. <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">36%</a> of businesses plan to start their holiday marketing about a month ahead of time, and 31% plan to do it up to three months ahead of time. If you want to stay ahead of your competition, then the earlier you start your Black Friday marketing the better.</p>
<h3>A smart Black Friday strategy connects you with customers when it matters most</h3>
<p>You can use Black Friday as an opportunity to place your business in front of customers when they‚Äôre ready to buy. For instance, purchases made directly in an app, rather than on a website or in-store, increased by <a href="https://appdevelopermagazine.com/in-app-purchases-surged-on-black-friday-2024/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">14%</a> during Black Friday last year. In this case, you might want to consider <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/instagram-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">launching an Instagram Shop</a> for the holiday season.</p>
<p>Being present on the right channels is crucial to your holiday success. <a href="https://scontent-den2-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.8562-6/517243945_736430135604467_9059314080577066169_n.pdf?_nc_cat=107&amp;ccb=1-7&amp;_nc_sid=e280be&amp;_nc_ohc=y5KHe56OXVgQ7kNvwEYIF_K&amp;_nc_oc=AdkrW_MYF3GQUaO2bD09OX2OJ48YQdRVsKYOFPVKaalqeKP0HA24-h88-pmBilLU6iM&amp;_nc_zt=14&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-den2-1.xx&amp;_nc_gid=2MB_GmGvPGgRgL0DwZA2mw&amp;oh=00_AfeKgBUwfiaICrqSz16ZY3WX8lf1ehfEjlOpNy2D3YMzqw&amp;oe=68F6E013" target="_blank" rel="noopener">63%</a> of shoppers say posts and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/scale-meta-ads-with-first-party-data" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ads across Meta-owned apps</a> are likely to influence their holiday purchases. <a href="https://scontent-den2-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.8562-6/517243945_736430135604467_9059314080577066169_n.pdf?_nc_cat=107&amp;ccb=1-7&amp;_nc_sid=e280be&amp;_nc_ohc=y5KHe56OXVgQ7kNvwEYIF_K&amp;_nc_oc=AdkrW_MYF3GQUaO2bD09OX2OJ48YQdRVsKYOFPVKaalqeKP0HA24-h88-pmBilLU6iM&amp;_nc_zt=14&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-den2-1.xx&amp;_nc_gid=2MB_GmGvPGgRgL0DwZA2mw&amp;oh=00_AfeKgBUwfiaICrqSz16ZY3WX8lf1ehfEjlOpNy2D3YMzqw&amp;oe=68F6E013" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Over half</a> of consumers look across Meta‚Äôs platforms for holiday research and evaluation. <a href="https://scontent-den2-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t39.8562-6/519201665_2256835098083571_8716989386968032493_n.pdf?_nc_cat=100&amp;ccb=1-7&amp;_nc_sid=e280be&amp;_nc_ohc=mSrmCsHsa3AQ7kNvwFU1ojw&amp;_nc_oc=AdnfDSu8gM-qywdooVTvygA7syEzFnLdXyCFKgQoAPVz4xrQ7g0o7EE5K4G2oQdWWvQ&amp;_nc_zt=14&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-den2-1.xx&amp;_nc_gid=r1783OEhHb8TrwBJA8Am3A&amp;oh=00_Aff0OyMAHJBkWK9VhrOBAIieJBQ0_oZAZxt-vy-S37gDxA&amp;oe=68F6DF5A" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Nearly 60%</a> of weekly Facebook and Instagram users prefer to get holiday shopping recommendations from <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/06/22/instagram-reels-ideas-for-businesses" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Reels</a>.</p>
<h3>Black Friday is the perfect time to test new marketing and advertising tactics</h3>
<p>You can use this time of year to try marketing and advertising strategies you may not have tried otherwise. If you do, you‚Äôre not alone. <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">42%</a> of businesses plan to try a new or different strategy for their Black Friday and Cyber Monday marketing and advertising campaigns this year.</p>
<p>For example, you could use Black Friday as an opportunity to refresh your website. <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">34%</a> of businesses say that <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/how-to-increase-website-speed" target="_blank" rel="noopener">website performance optimization</a> is their top priority when preparing for the holiday season.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/06/26/marketing-channels" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Other channels</a> increase in efficacy during Black Friday, too. <a href="https://woocommerce.com/posts/black-friday-stats-and-trends/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">23%</a> of businesses say <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/12/01/holiday-email-templates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">email marketing</a> is the most effective channel for Black Friday promotions, followed by <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/social-media-strategy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">organic social media marketing</a> with 21% finding this channel the most effective during the holidays.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-statistics.webp" alt="black friday marketing - statistics callout" width="899" height="665" class="aligncenter wp-image-95036 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-statistics.webp 899w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-statistics-480x355.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 899px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="when-to-start-black-friday-marketing"></div>
<h2>When should you start Black Friday marketing?</h2>
<p>Whether this time of year is your business‚Äôs busy or slow season, there are ways to make Black Friday work for your business. But it can be hard to know for sure exactly <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/when-should-you-start-holiday-marketing/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">when to start capitalizing on Black Friday</a> and the holiday season.</p>
<p>Remember, Black Friday isn‚Äôt just one day. It encompasses a series of days you can make moves on, known as ‚ÄúBlack Fiveday.‚Äù Let‚Äôs quickly review each key date within this timeframe:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Thanksgiving: </strong>The fourth Thursday in November, this holiday signifies the start of the holiday season for many. Most consumers will be eyeing holiday deals by this time.</li>
<li><strong>Black Friday:</strong> Immediately after Thanksgiving is Black Friday, the official holiday for seasonal shopping.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/small-business-saturday-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Small Business Saturday</strong></a><strong>: </strong>Next, after Black Friday, all small businesses should be taking advantage of this day that‚Äôs dedicated to encouraging consumers to shop small and work with local businesses.</li>
<li><strong>Sofa Sunday/Cyber Sunday: </strong>While the Sunday within this big week of deals doesn‚Äôt have a widely popular name or theme, many know it as ‚ÄúSofa Sunday‚Äù or ‚ÄúCyber Sunday‚Äù as shoppers make purchases virtually from the comfort of their homes.</li>
<li><strong>Cyber Monday:</strong> This is the final day of Black Fiveday, where customers will be searching for your business‚Äôs online offers.</li>
</ul>
<p>An honorable mention goes to Giving Tuesday, the day after Cyber Monday, which is all about giving back to your community, volunteering time with organizations that matter, and other philanthropic activities. You can still use Giving Tuesday to market your business or continue your holiday deals by showing customers how you care about causes that matter to your brand.</p>
<p>Basically, you‚Äôve got a whole week‚Äôs worth of marketing and advertising you‚Äôll have to prepare in order to squeeze all that you can out of Black Friday. You‚Äôll likely need some time in advance to be sure you‚Äôre set up for success.</p>
<p>While there‚Äôs no right or wrong way to start your Black Friday marketing and advertising, here are a few things to keep in mind when you begin planning:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.digitalcommerce360.com/2024/08/26/2024-holiday-shopping-season-survey/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Experts predict</a> shoppers will shop earlier this year to grab gifts before prices increase too much or inventory decreases. This year, <a href="https://www.insideradio.com/free/holiday-shopping-2024-plans-to-visit-big-box-retailers-up-20/article_39ec8590-6441-11ef-a741-6b0e5a1f0df3.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">28%</a> of consumers starting holiday shopping before Labor Day.</li>
<li><a href="https://localiq.com/blog/2022-holiday-marketing-tips/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">57%</a> of people plan to complete their holiday shopping before December.</li>
</ul>
<p>So, <strong>short answer for when to start your Black Friday marketing: As early as possible</strong>. However, don‚Äôt feel like you‚Äôre too late in the game if you haven‚Äôt started yet. When it comes to Black Friday marketing and advertising, <em>something</em> is always better than <em>nothing</em>. Don‚Äôt hesitate to get started as soon as you can, even if Black Friday is creeping up quick.</p>
<p>Lastly, it‚Äôs important to remember there are other <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/10/20/november-marketing-ideas" target="_blank" rel="noopener">key dates throughout November</a> that can pair nicely with your Black Friday promotions.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-november-1024x574.webp" alt="black friday marketing - example november ideas and promotions" width="1024" height="574" class="aligncenter wp-image-95041 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-november-980x550.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/black-friday-marketing-november-480x269.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="black-friday-marketing-and-advertising-tips"></div>
<h2>Black Friday marketing and advertising tips</h2>
<p>Check out these five Black Friday marketing tips to help you get on the right track for the season.</p>
<h3>Use a marketing calendar to get organized</h3>
<p>A <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/marketing-calendar/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">marketing calendar</a>, like the example below, can help you manage your marketing before, during, and after Black Fiveday. That way, you can decide which days you‚Äôll run certain campaigns, promotional teasers, and so on.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2026-marketing-calendar-november-1024x498.webp" alt="black friday marketing - calendar template preview" width="1024" height="498" class="aligncenter wp-image-95040 size-large" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2026-marketing-calendar-november-980x476.webp 980w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/2026-marketing-calendar-november-480x233.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f4c6.png" alt="üìÜ" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Download our free </strong><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/marketing-calendar?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2026MarketingCalendarGuide_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>2026 marketing calendar template</strong></a><strong> here!</strong></p>
<h3>Set short and long-term goals</h3>
<p>As you begin your Black Friday marketing preparations, set some goals to help your business stay on track. You‚Äôll likely want to set short-term goals to know what you want to achieve during the Black Fiveday period, as well as longer-term goals that connect the holiday season back to your year-round always-on marketing strategy.</p>
<p>The SMART (specific, measurable, achievable, relevant, and time-bound) goal structure can be useful during this step in your process.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-smart-chart-1-1-e1760985072440.webp" alt="smart goals examples - chart showing SMART components." width="797" height="381" class="aligncenter wp-image-88263 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-smart-chart-1-1-e1760985072440.webp 797w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/smart-goals-examples-wordstream-smart-chart-1-1-e1760985072440-480x270.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 797px, 100vw" /></p>
<h3>Pre-plan your Black Friday promotions</h3>
<p>Know what you‚Äôre going to offer during Black Friday ahead of time so you can easily brainstorm <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/01/black-friday-messages" target="_blank" rel="noopener">promotional messaging and copy</a>. Be sure to get all the details of any discounts, contests, or events ironed out so that your Black Friday marketing runs as smoothly as possible. Read on to get some ideas of what your business could offer during Black Friday.</p>
<h3>Be creative and have fun</h3>
<p>Black Friday is meant to be a fun, festive time of year. Don‚Äôt be afraid to lean into the spirit of the holidays when creating your marketing materials. For example, you might swap out your usual brand colors for a holiday-themed palette, or use <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/christmas-puns" target="_blank" rel="noopener">holiday puns</a> in your messaging.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Christmas-puns-wordstream-cute-puns-e1760985119284.webp" alt="Christmas puns - Instagram post with a cute pun." width="378" height="537" class="aligncenter wp-image-87632 size-full" /></p>
<h3>Use AI to ideate and create holiday magic</h3>
<p>Generative <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/best-ai-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI tools</a> can come in clutch for your Black Friday marketing and advertising. Just be sure you‚Äôre only using it to draft ideas or content, and that you give anything AI-generated a final, manual edit, so you‚Äôre putting out Black Friday marketing that‚Äôs aligned with your brand guidelines.</p>
<p>There are a ton of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-prompts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">holiday AI prompts</a> you can take advantage of, so don‚Äôt be afraid to ask AI tools for Black Friday promotion ideas, copywriting help, and more.</p>
